## Journal

Append entries to `{{.JournalPath}}`:

```json
{"round":1,"commit":"abc1234","desc":"what you investigated","confidence":"HIGH|MEDIUM|LOW","status":"progress","quality":"A|B|C","owner_scope":"...","blocked_by":"...","depends_on":["master-rebuild"],"can_split":true,"suggested_next":"...","dispatchable_slices":[{"title":"...","why":"...","mode":"develop|research","suggested_owner":"session-2","suggested_action":"dispatch|adopt","evidence":["/abs/path"]}]}
```

Quality rubric:
- A=strong evidence+tested counter-evidence+actionable
- B=reasonable but gaps remain
- C=preliminary flag for deepening

The extra blocker fields are optional unless you are stuck. If you are blocked, append a `status:"stuck"` entry with the blocker, dependency, ownership scope, and the next smallest useful split the master could dispatch. Never list your own session name in `depends_on`. If you have actionable next steps, prefer `dispatchable_slices` over prose so the master can either dispatch them or directly adopt them.

